Class MultiMap<Key,Value>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.kennesaw.cs4850.tools.MultiMap<Key,Value>
  • Type Parameters:
    Key - The key data type.
    Value - The value data type.

    public class MultiMap<Key,Value>
extends java.lang.Object
    A multimap data structure is a fast searching container that pairs a list of elements to a key. This differs from a normal map data structure with the ability to map multiple elements to one key.

    Full description of a multimap datastructure: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multimap
    Author:
    paulg
